The paper proposes a novel approach for automatic pain detection from facial expressions using Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) and Hidden Conditional Random Fields (HCRFs). This involves analyzing images of faces to estimate pain intensity levels and then using personalized models to estimate the Visual Analog Scale (VAS) for each person. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV), Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Multimedia (cs.MM), and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
